 of this direct connection. We feel the presence of Guru Pashay. And then of course, we have the

00:11:51.940 --> 00:12:01.860
 skillful means of the visualization. So, number one, feeling the presence. And I think if we're

00:12:01.860 --> 00:12:10.020
 truly connected with our joy, our appreciation, our bodhicitta, our devotion, and openness,

00:12:10.020 --> 00:12:18.980
 you know, then that's number one important. So if that element is there, that's good.

00:12:21.140 --> 00:12:28.820
 And then, however, I'd also just encourage too, I mean, these are all skillful means practices.

00:12:28.820 --> 00:12:36.180
 These are all specific instructions that Guru Padmasambhava, the living Buddha of this time,

00:12:36.180 --> 00:12:47.060
 gave us. And so there's, there's very skillful, powerful reasons for working with our habitual

00:12:47.060 --> 00:12:57.540
 patterns that I'd say if we can, you know, staying with the feeling of the presence

00:12:57.540 --> 00:13:07.300
 and with our bodhicitta and devotion, can gently, gently, you know, not ignore our ability to

00:13:07.300 --> 00:13:16.420
 develop our concentration and our visualization qualities, then we should, then we should do that,

00:13:16.420 --> 00:13:23.540
 you know, if we can just spend, try to visualize a little bit as instructed, then that's also good.

00:13:23.540 --> 00:13:31.700
 So I think it's a little bit both ways, not being too tight or too loose, or, you know, but staying

00:13:31.700 --> 00:13:39.860
 with the practice and really working on developing again, our concentration, as well as our non

00:13:39.860 --> 00:13:48.500
 distraction, along with our devotion and big bodhicitta, and just being open for that.

00:13:48.500 --> 00:13:55.940
 And then with this particular dissolution at the end, I think what Rinpoche is, they describe

00:13:56.820 --> 00:14:02.260
 in "Illuminating the Path" and then Dodhrim Rinpoche does in other texts too, there's different

00:14:02.260 --> 00:14:02.660
 ways

00:14:02.660 --> 00:14:11.300
 we can dissolve this, you know, and one is where Guru Rinpoche, you know, dissolves into light

00:14:11.300 --> 00:14:18.020
 and then enters into our heart, you know, and that's usually through the crown coming down,

00:14:18.020 --> 00:14:27.700
 again, through what? Our central channel into our heart channel, into our heart, which again is

00:14:27.700 --> 00:14:28.020
 said,

00:14:28.020 --> 00:14:32.980
 the heart chakra is where our Buddha nature resides.

00:14:32.980 --> 00:14:43.140
 The other is that we as "Yeshisojal" just go forward and dissolve into

00:14:43.140 --> 00:14:50.740
 Guru Rinpoche's heart. So who's going forward? Who's coming? Again, I think it's very open in

00:14:50.740 --> 00:14:58.980
 reality, which way we're going, but so do what's comfortable, but my main point is try to follow,

00:14:58.980 --> 00:15:05.780
 do the visualization as it's instructed, I think is really good for all of us, but not being too

00:15:05.780 --> 00:15:13.060
 tight and we have also part of this visualization is also again, right, is so much remembering,

00:15:13.060 --> 00:15:19.540
 remembering the purity, we're in the pure land as Vajrayogini.

00:15:19.540 --> 00:15:27.700
 So there's no reason to doubt, we're really with our practice fundamentally,

00:15:27.700 --> 00:15:33.460
 we're trying to put aside all of our doubt and hesitation when we're practicing.

00:15:35.780 --> 00:15:42.660
 All of our mundane conceptions and habitual patterns, we're releasing and connecting with

00:15:42.660 --> 00:15:50.820
 what's fresh and true to the best of our abilities. And so part of that is visualizing ourselves as

00:15:50.820 --> 00:16:00.580
 Vajrayogini in pure land with Guru Rinpoche right here with us, which is the fact all the time,

00:16:00.580 --> 00:16:08.500
 I mean, that's the point of the teachings that that's not some story. Our story, our make believe

00:16:08.500 --> 00:16:16.420
 is our obstruction to that we haven't recognized that what that truly means and how that already

00:16:16.420 --> 00:16:25.940
 is, right? So even on that degree too, as far as visualization, we don't have to think that if

00:16:25.940 --> 00:16:33.860
 even if we don't see ourselves literally according to the instructions, or we might be in a room

00:16:33.860 --> 00:16:34.660
 with

00:16:34.660 --> 00:16:44.820
 the furnishings of this particular world in this particular time, we don't need to recoil from

00:16:44.820 --> 00:16:51.700
 that, we can know that is inseparable from the pure land. And I think that's a really important

00:16:51.700 --> 00:16:57.380
 point that the teachers make with our visualization, you know, we're not trying to have a big

00:16:57.380 --> 00:16:58.420
 disconnect,

00:16:58.420 --> 00:17:06.100
 we're trying to just have a fuller connect with how things are. And then kind of along those lines,

